inn1.comm: short of a length angling into the hips, Guptill misses the glance but the ball goes off his thigh past the keeper for a couple of legbyes
a length ball pitching outside off stump and angling into the right-hander, Guptill stays back and steers to third man
wait, wait, yes yes, that's the call from McCullum after going back and opening the face and pushing the length ball towards point, he wanted to see if the ball got past the diving fielder
pushed on the front foot, towards mid on
a length ball outside off, Guptill stays in his crease and punches to cover point
such a sedate first over from New Zealand! Guptill gets on the front foot and defends a good length ball. Hazlewood gave them no room or length to work with

short of a length and outside off, that ball disappears to the point boundary, it burst through Maxwell's fingers as he reached for the catch over his head, that must have stung so much, McCullum absolutely hammered the cut shot, so harsh to call that a dropped catch

the square boundary on the other side now, swivelling and pulling the short ball so flat and so hard, it was only a few metres to the left of the long leg fielder but he had no chance, a one-bounce four
steered behind point for a single
driven off the back foot to cover
good length on off and middle stump, defended from the crease with a straight bat
tries to drive a good length ball from the crease as it nips into him a touch and gets an inside edge behind square leg
clears his front foot to try and smash the ball down the ground, mis-timed it to mid-on, Hazlewood not giving him any width or length to hit. Seemed to hold his back a little after that shot

shot! A nimble charge down the track and towards leg to convert the good length into a full one, he then frees his arms to launch the ball over the extra cover boundary with a fierce drive, inside-out and so balanced despite all the hectic movement
swipes across the line but can't beat midwicket
driven hard and straight off the front foot, hits the bowler's legs
catch it in the stands! McCullum gets on the front foot and swivels to hook the bouncer with a lightning quick swing of the bat, that's far over long leg
driven so hard towards cover where the fielder dives to his right in the circle to save the boundary
good length around off stump, played back to the bowler with calm
in the air towards short cover, just out of the reach of the fielder diving to his left, Guptill pushed away from his body at the ball and did not time it well
good length just outside off, defended on the front foot
good length with some room outside off, Guptill tries to pull but is beaten, he's not yet hit his stride today, has Guptill. But he can afford to take his time for a bit
a fuller ball around off stump, played off the front foot to mid off
played off the pads towards square leg
and Scott Boland goes back over his head, McCullum has planted his front foot forward and smashed a full ball far over the straight boundary with a blur of his bat

bowled him! What a lift for Boland! McCullum charged him again but this time the length was not full and McCullum's swing connected with nothing, Boland hit the top of off stump. The fans at the Cake Tin rise to give McCullum a cheer as he walks off
a cheer for his first run, Williamson dabbed it off the back foot to third man
punched to cover off the back foot
good length on off and middle, played off the front foot to mid on
good length again, a splendid comeback after that first ball six, Guptill moves forward and blocks
moves back and across to play a length ball towards cover
a fuller ball outside off, Williamson strides forward and shoulders arms
good length on a wicket to wicket line, Williamson gets behind it and defends
he moves forward and across towards the off side and seemed to slip a little in his crease, and so Williamson let it go
the bouncer, and Williamson ducks under it
good length outside of stump, Williamson strides forward and shoulders arms, Hastings has bowled a maiden

and Guptill drives a full ball firmly and low to the bowler's left, Hazlewood stoops to try and stop it but can't get down quickly enough, was that in the air? I think Hazlewood got fingertips on it, again it's a hard chance so a tough drop.
played to square leg
punched off the back foot to cover point, really good lines and lengths today
not that time, Guptill moves forward and to leg to make room and drove the full ball clean over long off with a powerful swing of the bat, first boundary for him today
moves back and across to whip a good length ball through square leg but the length was not short enough, he gets hit on the thigh
stays in his crease and thumps a short of a length ball through cover, not perfectly timed but still quick enough to beat two chasing fielders
good length outside off, Williamson is in a watchful mood and he watchfully lets it go
nothing watchful about this though! He lunges for a really wide one outside off, but it is so wide that he can't make contact with a rash swipe
Williamson is a bit edgy today, Australia have given him nothing, bowling outside off with a packed field. Williamson flirts with a good length ball outside off and is beaten
again the line is well outside off on a good length, they are giving him nothing straight to play on the leg, he bottom edges the ball close on the off side, was looking to play towards point
driven off the front foot towards cover
this time there is more width on offer and the length is a bit shorter, Williamson cuts off the back foot behind point, but third man runs to his right and cuts off the boundary
full and wide outside off, Guptill flays it towards the first point with a fierce square drive, Bailey gets behind the ball and stops it
good length just outside off stump, defended on the front foot on the off side
moves forward to meet a full ball angling into him and pushes towards mid-on

good length on a tight line just outside off, Williamson moves back and across towards the off side and dabs the ball gently towards leg. Wade came forward and collected the throw and took off the bails, not quite sure what was going on there, Wade was asking the square leg umpire something about where Williamson was
most of the fielders are on the off side so Williamson moves back and across quickly to pull a length ball through square leg
full ball outside off, driven on the front foot to long off
cut off the back foot behind point
Williamson moves back and across to defend a good length ball
blocked off the back foot towards the off side
Williamson adjusts to the off side plan, moving back and across to pull a short of a length ball through midwicket for his first boundary

and he counters again, stepping down the track to hit the ball from a fuller length over mid-on, not timed perfectly but well enough ... it's a 6-3 off side field and Williamson is making the play to hit through the leg side
defended on the leg side
wider outside off stump, played off the back foot to cover point
that skidded on, keeping low on a wicket to wicket line, Guptill was shaping to pull but then had to hurry through the shot to avoid an lbw appeal
pushed off the front foot to long off
a flatter ball outside off, Williamson goes back and pulls towards long on
driven off the front foot through covers for two, a fuller length and Guptill came forward to meet it
strides out and drives a flighted ball along the ground through cover

what a shot that is! The gap between short third man and backward point was so small but Williamson went back into his crease and found it with the most precise late cut you can hope to see. Such class, wasn't a bad ball at all
driven to long off for a single
jumps back and across to whip a good length ball from off stump, can't get past midwicket
moves back and across again to work the ball off his hips to square leg
Williamson moves across his crease towards the off side once again to flick a good length ball towards midwicket, there's no seam movement on offer to threaten the leading edge, can't find a gap
played on the leg side again, taking the ball from outside off, once again he can't find the gap
this time Boland is a little too straight, Williamson moves across and flicks towards backward square leg
driven back to the bowler from the crease
comes forward and drives the ball to long off
defended from the crease on the off side
Williamson goes back and cuts late again, this time the fielder at backward point moves quickly to his left to field it
steps out and works the ball to midwicket, Zampa isn't turning the ball much at all

Warner runs a long way to his left from long off and slides, he got to the ball but lets it go through him for four! Williamson had come out of his crease to cover drive a full ball, made use of the width outside off
a length ball on the pads, Guptill picks it up off the front foot and lofts it clean towards the wide long on boundary
driven off the front foot towards cover
stays in his crease and plays the ball to point
defended from the crease on the off side
moves back and across and turns the ball through square leg
steps forward and outside leg stump and then adjusts because the length is not full enough to drive, Williamson waits and steers towards third man
nudged off the back foot on the leg side
a full toss, Guptill hits it in the air but it falls short of long on
Williamson goes back to a good length ball and punches to long on
defended back to the bowler
driven off the front foot to the bowler's left, Zampa dives to field
cut off the back foot to deep cover
short ball at no real pace, Guptill meets it on the front foot and pulls to the deep midwicket boundary
short of a length just outside off, Guptill tries to pull again but mis-times it to long off for a single
a direct hit from midwicket after Guptill asks Williamson to wait, Warner had swooped on the push towards mid-on and under-armed it while diving

caught at deep cover! Guptill came out of his crease and moved towards leg to smash a good length ball from outside off down the ground, the bat turned in his hand as he made contact and he ended up slicing the ball towards the cover boundary, where Khawaja settled under the catch. He judged that well, because the ball seemed to be swirling and it wasn't straightforward
a fuller ball on off and middle, Williamson drives straight off the front foot between the stumps and the non-striker, the fielder at mid-on cuts it off
Nicholls gets going right away, tucking a short of a length ball off his hips through square leg
an appeal for lbw after Nicholls tries to sweep but misses, that hit the pad outside off stump though
shorter length, Nicholls moves quickly back into his crease and pulls the ball through midwicket
the googly outside off, but the length is short and Nicholls pulls off the back foot in the air past Maxwell at midwicket
played off the back foot to midwicket
good length and line on off stump, Williamson moves forward and blocks
moves forward and drives the ball to long off for a single
good length on a wicket to wicket line, Williamson gets behind the line and defends
a length ball outside off, Williamson waits in his crease and cuts through point

that's a loose ball and a loose shot and a loose dismissal, Marsh is thrilled with his second wicket. He bowled a short and wide ball outside off from around the wicket, with a cross seam so it gripped the pitch a bit. It might have been called wide had Nichollls let it go but he chased it with a half-hearted waft at edged through to Wade. If you're going to slash, slash hard ...
wide outside off, Elliott is not chasing after this, lets it go
a fuller ball on off and middle, Elliott moves across in his crease and turns the ball off the pads behind square
tucked through square leg for a single again
goes back and cuts a length ball so well and so late, Hastings covers a lot of ground to his right from third man and dives to prevent the boundary, that was timed superbly
tucked off the hips through square leg to bring up the 100
short of a length outside off, the batsman lets it go
good ball, good length and good line just outside off, holds its line too, Elliott prods from the crease with no footwork and is beaten
lets this one go outside off

the camera has trouble keeping up with the ball as it screams across the fast outfield to the backward point boundary, there was width on offer outside off and Elliott used it to cut the short of a length ball so hard
driven back to the bowler on the front foot, Marsh fields in his follow through
short of a length on the hips, he misses the glance but will get leg byes behind square
short of a length and wide outside off, Elliott doesn't time the cut so well this time, hitting it in the air and behind point
a full ball on leg stump, clipped off the pads through square leg
good length just outside off, played with soft hands towards cover point for one
good length on off and middle, worked off the pads towards midwicket
moves forward to play the ball on the off side, he then checks his shot and stops it, and ends up playing it towards point
steps forward and short-arm pulls the length ball through square leg
short ball, Williamson swivels and pulls the ball towards long leg
nearly in the blockhole outside off, driven on the front foot to mid off
good length angling in from outside off stump, driven on the front foot towards cover
gets on the front foot to slap the short of a length ball through point but mis-times the shot
a full ball outside off, driven on the front foot to mid off
short of a length outside off, Williamson jumps back and plays the ball towards point
played with a straight bat towards the bowler
strides forward to a full ball outside off and drives through cover
stays back to a short of a length ball and opens the face late to steer towards third man
good length on off, played off the back foot to midwicket
full and attacking the off stump, defended on the front foot
this is even fuller on off, eased to deep cover
rising short ball outside off, KW loads up for a pull. He decides against it at the last moment and jabs it back to the bowler
good length and just a shade outside off, run down to third man for one
zipping through the channel, KW was in two minds there as well. Hanging his bat out before pulling it away
full on off, square-driven for a single
pitched up and outside off, tapped down to long-off. Smoothly done
KW jumps down, meets this on a half-volley and drives down the ground for a couple. KW calls for it and gets it
tossed up and curls in, googly from Zampa. KW skipped down again. He misjudged the pace there; the ball stopped a little. KW adjusts, checks his flick, and chips it over midwicket
slides on off, defended
pushed through, patted to cover
darted at 93ks, driven nicely to sweeper cover
full and outside off at 140ks, square-driven for one more. NZ ticking along
pitched up on off, KW shuffles across and flicks to midwicket
dug shorter and outside off as KW steps away, opening up the off side. He rides it quietly to third man
full on middle, defended onto the pitch
Elliott sways back and secures a single of his own to third man
an appeal for caught behind, not given. Back of a length and outside off, KW targets the leg side with a flick. He connects only with thin air. No inside snick, there
flatter and quicker, stabbed back to Zampa
rank full toss on middle, duly dispatched over midwicket for a six
slides on outside off, punchily driven through point
down the track and crunched to short cover; the fielder flings to his right and makes a smart stop
flighted on off, KW dances out, and chips it over mid-off. Smartly done, this time by the batsman
straighter one, pushed back to Zampa with a straight bat. Zampa has a shy at the stumps, Elliott doesn't jump out of the way. He shields himself with a straightish bat, again
dabbed with soft hands to mid-on, the pair sneak a single
pushed through vacant mid-on, again

Hastings clangs a chance? KW uses his feet and slices it off an outside edge. Hastings may have been a touch late to pick up and attack the ball. The ball lands in front of him at short third man, despite a dive
goes straight on outside off, Maxi finds the outside edge, which wanders away through vacant slip
flat and quick at the base of off, jabbed to cover
Maxi shortens his length, punched back, Maxi dives full-length to his right and stops the ball
KW jumps out again, he nearly ran past this slider. He just manages to squeeze it to short third man
pushed calmly down the ground. More like KW
dug in shorter and outside off, cut firmly to the off-side sweeeper
looped up full, driven down the ground. Sharp running between the wickets. They collect two
shortish with extra bounce outside off, flat-batted down to long-off
straighter on off, run away towards point with soft hands
full on middle, down the pitch and laced down the ground. KW met the pitch and presented a straight bat
darted outside off, chopped to point
defended back to the bowler
full and straight, clipped through midwicket
fired flat and quick, KW goes right back now, uses the depth of the crease, and cracks a cut between the covers and point. He made room and middled it. KW acknowledges his fifty
glanced off the pads behind square
whoa! Fullish and outside off, KW caresses it beautifully over extra cover, sending it skimming over the boundary with some wristwork

KW can't hit the repeat button, Zampa celebrates his maiden ODI wicket. Nicely lobbed up outside off, KW drives in the air again, this time he picks out Smith at extra-cover. Big, big wicket. KW spins his head away in disappointment
flat and quick, punched to midwicket on the back foot
turned off the pads through square leg
tossed up on middle, picked away to midwicket
drifting down leg, as the batsman topples over the flick. Wide
flighted on middle, patted quietly to mid-on
loose ball into the pads, Anderson uses the pace of Maxi, and guides it to fine leg
Maxi strays into the pads of Elliott now, he misses the flick
hint of turn back in, pushed back to Maxi
hurled shorter at 90ks, clipped through midwicket
slides on outside off, back-foot punch through the covers
Elliott uses his feet and works it to the leg side
shorter on middle, forced through midwicket

Elliott does a KW. Zampa gives this loads of air, tempts Elliott into an airy stroke. The ball dips, and the batsman drives it in the air.... into the lap of Maxi who takes it calmly despite a little juggle. Two in two for the debutant
drifts in on middle and leg, defensively pushed to mid-on
chopped from outside off through backward point. Ronchi gets off the mark with two
back of a length on off, slapped through point
full and just a shade outside off, driven along the carpet to long-off
darted quick, tapped back
dug in short on off, right in the pulling arc. The long hop is smacked flat over midwicket
short on middle, played back to the bowler
dragged short again, pulled, though not firmly, to cow corner
flighted on middle, pushed back to Maxi
hurrying ball on off, chopped through point
full on middle, lofted hit to long-on
skiddy ball on off, defended on the back foot
heading down leg, swept to backward square leg
tickled off the pads to long leg
this one rushes onto the batsman, chopped through point
flighted and full on off and middle, driven hard to mid-off
nice and full outside off, outside edge taken, but it does not carry to the diving Wade
Anderson welcomes Boland back with a powerful short-arm jab. Dug in outside off from round the wicket, muscled over midwicket
shortish and ducks back in, Anderson jams it on his pad off an inside edge
another rising ball, angled in, Anderson hops and diffuses it in front of his feet
full on middle, Anderson hangs back and nudges a single to point by opening the face of the bat
back of a length on off, run away towards point
banged in on middle, fended back to the bowler
shorter and a hint of width as Anderson frees his arms and cuts in front of square, there is protection in the deep
back of a length on off, Ronchi steps forward and plays it to point
full on the stumps, driven to mid-on
twirled off the pads through backward square leg. Good use of the wrists
short and wide outside off, Ronchi does not take advantage of the width. He skips back and cuts it straight to point
Ah! Anderson can leave the ball as well. This is a tight one. Angled in, almost shaved the off stump
full and outside off, Anderson won't ignore this. Flayed past cover

another soft dismissal, another failure for Ronchi. Back of a length, Ronchi may have misjudged the pace on this. The back-of-a-length ball stopped on him as he shaped to flick. He can only chip it to Mitch Marsh at mid-on; chest-high catch
left alone outside off
shorter on off, fended to leg
short and attacking the body, fended behind square
straying into the legs, flicked impressively past mid-on
back of a length and holds its line on middle, Anderson replies with a dead bat
wicket-to-wicket line, Anderson hangs back and blocks to the off side
bouncer, whizzes outside off, Anderson rocks his head out of the way
banged in on off, climbs sharply and hits the bat as opposed to the bat hitting ball. Hastings can bowl a heavy ball
back of a length, guided to point
shorter and just a shade outside off, neatly dabbed down fine on the off side, to third man
the batsman has a nervy waft in the channel and is beaten
short of a length on middle, blocked on the back foot
short again, this rushes onto Santner, who takes on Hazlewood at mid on. Urgent single
dug in on middle, fended to leg
back of a length and just a shade outside off, played to point
short on middle, dropped defensively onto the pitch
bumper sails over the ducking batsman. Umpire Billy says one for the over
dragged short and outside off, pulled away to deep square leg
chopped from a fourth-stump line to third man
banged in, bouncer, Santner avoids it. This one parachutes over him. Wide
length and outside off, Santner secures a single to third man
width outside off, Anderson throws his hands at it, slashing it to third man off a dirty, thick outside edge
back of a length on middle, Anderson presses across off in defence

he comes back and takes down Anderson. Full and swerves away with the angle outside off. Anderson does not want to hold back. He throws his bat at it. He can only settle with a thin tickle behind to Wade. NZ are falling away
Hazlewood greets the new man with a bumpy short ball outside off, Milne sways back and lets it pass by dropping his wrists
back of a length on middle, nudged to the leg side
picked away off the pads through backward square leg
full and straight, proper flick behind square

short and outside off, chopped to the covers, where Warner takes a couple of steps to his right. That was the key there before the full-stretch dive. He picks up the ball, throws in one motion, but can't nail the stumps down. A direct hit could have dismissed Milne
full and outside off, tapped through the covers. Milne gets across to the other end
top-edged two rows back for a six! Short ball, rushes onto Santner, who is rapped high on the bat, as he shapes to hook. The helpful top edge goes all the way
short on middle, fended carefully

two fielders converge. The ball goes straight in and slips out Smith's hands. Another hurrying short ball as Santner sends another top edge swirling in the air. The man (Zampa) from the deep sprints in, Smith tracks back from midwicket. He gets into a side-on position, but reprieves Santner. Perhaps, that was Zampa's catch. He backed out once Smith prowled in
zippy short ball, fended onto the pitch
dabbed to the cover-point region
full and ducks back in, squirted to leg off an inside edge
short ball, Santner rolls his wrists to keep the pull down. Hit to deep midwicket
full and not too wide outside off, dabbed through soft hands through vacant slip
banged in short on off, Milne gets on top of the bounce and pulls it strongly over backward square leg. Shot of a proper batsman
yorker, squeezed out to the leg side for one
short and outside off, Milne can'r run this to third man
similar ball, this time he leans back and dabs a cut to third man
back of a length on off, defended
full on middle, slapped back to the bowler, who deflects it off his boot to mid-off
Hastings goes wide of the crease and angles it in. Full on off, milked down the ground
dug in short on middle, Santner does not hold back. Unleashes a full swing and pastes it over midwicket
Boland hunts for a yorker, ends up bowling a low full toss on off, which is belted through mid-off
full on middle, flicked straight to midwicket
yorker aimed at the base of off, dug out
Milne manufactures a full toss by stepping out. Thumped to long-on
Boland follows the full toss with another pinpoint yorker. This was why Boland was picked. Squeezed out
Milne skips down the track again, meets a full toss, and drills it down to Warner at long-on
full on middle, hit down to long-on
low full toss on off, slugged over cow corner as Santner pushes NZ past 250
Hastings changes his pace, 119ks slower ball. Santner can't manufacture his own pace here. Dragged to midwicket for one
low full toss outside off, crashed to deep cover
near yorker on middle and leg, jabbed through midwicket. They hare across for a couple. Excellent running

Milne ventures across the off stump and misses the lap-scoop. Hit outside the line of off. Not given. Australia, however, want a review. Hastings' front foot is fine. It was a long way outside the line. Billy's call is vindicated
full but Milne makes room, advances and belts it to long-off
full again, drilled down to long-on. Warner cuts in close, gathers the ball, throws the stumps down, but they take the second off the rihochet
full again, not a yorker. Milne hangs deep in the crease and whips through midwicket
full and in the slot again, Milne swings and drags it through midwicket
Santner now drags from outside off to midwicket
back of a length and outside off, hoicked to long-on
length and outside off, chopped through the covers
overpitched on off, Milne nearly swings himself off his feet. Thrashed to long-on
yorker just a shade outside off, Milne can't jam it out
well, that was simple! Fierecly struck but straight down the throat of the Australian captain. End of a sparky cameo from Milne. He dances out to a length ball and drills it to Smith at cover
full on middle, driven hard to mid-on
knocked him over. The middle stump is flattened. Back of a length, straight on middle, Henry clears his front leg. Goes for a wild, dirty slog, and misses. Hazlewood pounds the middle stump
super sharp work! Warner sprints to his left, dives full-length from long-off to stop this firm drive
cracked down to long-on
back of a length and outside off, swung over to the long-on fence
yorker just wide of the off stump, he can't dig it out
Santner comes down and yorks himself now. This is dug back to the bowler
good bowling from Boland. Blackhole ball on off, squeezed through the off side for one
full and angled away outside off, Santner loads up for a massive swing and does not connect
wide yorker, past the tramline, off-side wide
full on off, Santner sends it thudding to long-on
back of a length on middle, Boult spins away outside leg and hacks it towards long-on

it's all happening at the Cake Tin (Bill Lawry's voice)! yorker from Hazlewood, Santner can't dig it out. The caught-behind appeal is nipped in the bud. Boult sets off for a single. He is more than halfway down the pitch. Wade collects the ball and ferries it to Hazlewood, who can't under-arm flick it onto the stumps at the non-striker's end
Boult jumps outside leg again, slogged through midwicket
low full toss outside off, driven to long-off. Warner swoops on the ball and keeps it to one. What a athleticism

inn2.comm: swinging into the pads, Khawaja sends it racing to to the backward square leg boundary with a flick
sliding into the pads again, clipped to midwicket
full and angled in on middle, blocked to the leg side
Khawaja snaps his wrists again to meet this full ball. Exquisitely flicked in the gap between midwicket and mid-on
Boult shortens his length on off, Khawaja hops and defends to cover
back of a length on middle, Khawaja sits back and blocks
banged in short and outside off, Warner says "hello" as he pulls it strongly over midwicket. That was sent thudding to the boundary. And it came off the bottom of the bat
Milne bends this back in on a back of a length, blocked
back of a length, pushed to cover
nudged off the hips to square leg
shortish and outside off, dabbed towards point
short, wicket-to-wicket line, blocked on the back foot
swings down the leg side, Boult's line is wonky. Wide
back of a length, turned to square leg on the back foot
rising short ball outside off, Khawaja is beaten on the cut
Khawaja leans back and succeeds in cutting this short ball behind point
full on middle, Warner steps away outside leg, frees up the off side, and lifts it over cover, he says "hello" to Boult as well
back of a length on middle, Warner is more sedate now as he blocks it back to the bowler
short of a length, Warner is up on his tippy toes as he punches to the right of mid-off
short and just a shade outside off, mistimed cut to mid-off
rising short ball outside off, quelled to the cover-point region
one-bounce four! Banged in outside off, Warner leaps off his feet and ramps it over, easily beating third man
short and on the hips, Warner swivels on the back foot and pull-flicks to deep midwicket
overpitched outside off, forward and crunched to cover
Henry reverts to the shorter length, Khawaja rolls his wrists and controls a pull to deep midwicket
short, no swing on off, the batsman leans back and cuts through backward point
Boult slides a yorker down the leg side, second wide from Boult
short and wide outside off, Warner slashes with brute force. Hit flat and hard over over point. He exploits the short boundary
half-volley length on middle, pushed down the ground
clipped off the pads through square leg
pretty full on middle, patted to mid-on
back of a length and outside off, punched sqaure between backward point and cover-point
back of a length outside off, Khawaja dismisses it to the midwicket boundary with a swipe
even shorter, blocked back to the bowler
shortish on middle, guided late to point
pitched up and outside off, driven handsomely to the right of mid-off. Are the IPL franchises watching this?
and four more! Veering into the pads, glanced to the right of short fine leg, easily done
full on middle, solid push to mid-off. Australia motor to 50 in six overs
drifting down leg, diverted off the pads to short fine leg
slanted down leg again, this is a wide
quicker outside off, flat-batted down to long-off
Khawaja steps out, KW pulls his length back. Stabbed to cover
too close to the off stump for a cut. Chopped off the back foot to cover again
beats mid-on to his right! Khawaja steps out, manufactures a full toss and unfurls another drive from the top draw
back of a length on middle, this is quietly turned to midwicket on the back foot
shorter on middle, played back
dug in short on off, pulled firmly to Nicholls who is patrolling the square boundary on the leg side
full and rushes onto the batsman at 141ks, not short at all. But Warner aims a pull. He is rapped on the pad. It pitched outside leg and umpire S Ravi agrees with me
full and aimed at off, hacked to leg off an inside edge
short at 140ks, thuds into the thigh pad off an inside edge as Warner does not get hold of the pull
too full and straight, whipped in the gap at midwicket
Khawaja comes down and pushes it to deep mid-on
fractionally short on off, whacked over long-on on the back foot
low full toss on middle, clipped to the leg side
fired full, jabbed to the off side
Warner goes deep in the crease, slaps from outside off to cover
floated up on middle, blocked back to the bowler on the front foot
back of a length and outside off, punched to the cover region
short with extra bounce, beats the flick and socks the thigh
rising ball on middle, Warner is up on his tippy toes as he fends to cover. Milne cranks up to 150ks, he topples over his followthrough
banged in short, Warner cranks it up now. He pulls and sends it clattering into the grandstand. One-handed take in the crowd
back of a length rushing ball, blocked to off
another short ball, Warner backs away a touch and rides it to point
slides on middle, Khawaja camps back and works through midwicket
Warner skips out, takes a step forward rather, Santner shortens his length and hits the pad
knocked through square leg
tossed up, glanced to backward square leg
tossed up, worked through square leg
flat on the leg stump, swept to deep square leg
length ball, pushed to cover
clipped off the pads through backward square leg
split-finger slower one drifting down leg as the batsman misses the flick
the man at cover dives to his right to stop this push
umpire Billy ducks and takes evasive action. Dug in short, Khawaja smashes a pull over the square-leg umpire. He did well to swerve his head out of the way. That went like a rocket to the boundary
good length and outside off, tapped past cover
too full and outside off, laced over cover for four
full on middle, defended
Khawaja stays back and chops to backward point
top strike from Warner. Mid-off is up in the circle. He goes over the fielder with a lofted hit and brings up his fifty
lap-pulled away to fine leg
flighted on middle, Khawaja flicks over midwicket. Nearly plops a catch to deep midwicket
straight ball on middle, defended on the front foot
back of a length, hit to long-on
full and outside off, run away behind point
pitched up and just outside off, square-driven for two. Good urgency
too full, picked away to midwicket
back of a length on off, Khawaja steps across off and manipulates it with the wrists behind square on the leg side
slides on middle and leg, dropped defensively to the leg side
darted on leg, swept away behind square
non-turning ball on the stumps, pushed to long-on
half-tracker outside off, rocked back and pulled to deep midwicket
width outside off, Warner flays at it and ends up carving it over point off a thick outside edge
flighted on middle, Warner secures another easy single down the ground
back of a length and just outside off, caressed to the left of the diving backward point fielder
overpitched and outside off, driven sweetly to sweeper cover
short and outside off, Khawaja allows the ball to come to him and then chops to third man
width outside off, Warner lashes it to sweeper cover
maiden ODI fifty for Khawaja. He is in bumper form. Full and outside off, he leans forward and drives it gloriously to sweeper cover
dug in outside off, Warner gets on top of the bounce and pulls to deep midwicket
glanced off the hips through deep square leg

fifty and out! Chipped back to the bowler off a leading edge. Drifting into the pads again, Khawaja targets the leg side with a gentle little flick. He can only spoon a return catch to Santner who breaks the rousing opening partnership
he sets to work immediately. Full and straight, busy flick through midwicket
flat full ball, pushed to cover
knocked off the hips to midwicket
nice and full, drifts in, Smith defends with a dead-straight bat
Henry almost created a wicket! Full, stops on the batsman, chipped just wide of Milne at mid-off
Henry pounds the deck, the line is outside off, left alone
Smith gets across and defends
back of a length, punched to cover
full on the stumps, patted to mid-on
full and snakes in with the angle, Smith looks to drive. He gets an inside edge that rolls to the leg side
short ball on middle, back-foot punch through the covers, whistles away to the boundary
shortish again, pulled away to deep midwicket
drifting onto the pads, worked behind square on leg
straight ball on middle, eased to long-off
loopier on off, Smith tips forward in defence
arm-ball snakes in, punched to short midwicket
short and outside off, Warner rides the bounce and helps it to third man
cracker of a stop. Anderson at mid-off flings to his right, full-length dive and prevents a four. This was crunched by Smith

this wasn't crunched. This was just edged. Cracker of a stop followed by a cracker of a  catch. Full and outside off, Smith feels for the ball and outside-edges it towards first slip. But Ronchi dives full-stretch to his right and snaps up the one-handed catch. Ronchi may have lost it with the bat, but he still has it with the gloves

double-blow from Henry! He lets out a massive roar. Bailey is gone for a golden duck. He went unsold in the IPL auction as well. This is a gem. Back of a length, snakes back in a long way off the seam. Rips through the gate and hits the top of off
back of a length and nips in on off again, Maxi inches forward and defends
lifting ball outside off, ignored. End of a top-quality over
full on the stumps, drilled down to long-on. Boult actually deflected it away in his followthrough; ump Billy was in the firing line again, this time at the non-striker's end
banged in short and outside off, pull and a miss
back of a length on off, pushed to point
clipped off the pads through backward square leg
full on middle, tapped to mid-off
full and comes in, jabbed to mid-on
good length on middle, run away towards point
full and straight, nurdled through midwicket
back of a length and slants away outside off, eased to sweeper cover
back of a length on middle, swatted to deep midwicket
snaffled down the leg side? ump Ravi shakes his head. Drifting down leg, it brushed the pad on its way to the keeper. No bat/glove involved
short ball on off, defended
full on middle and leg, whipped through backward square leg
full and angled away outside off, drilled in the air, to the right of mid-off
Boult has Maxi chopping on. Boult flashes a smile. Fractionally short, not much room either, Maxi shapes to pull. He gets a thick inside edge that rebounds off pad and hits the furniture
full and angled away, swing and a miss
good length and outside off, Marsh hoists his bat above his shoulder and leaves now
shortish on middle, pulled to midwicket
full on middle, driven through mid-off
shortish and outside off, Marsh throws his bat at it. Jabbed to cover
full toss below the waistline, chipped to midwicket
back of a length on off, pushed towards point
pitched up and outside off, no shot offered
back of a length, top of off line, blocked
dug in short as Warner spins on the back foot and pulls it behind square
back of a length and angling away, uppish drive in the big gap at point
back of a length, defended to cover
pretty full on off, pushed to cover
back of a length, stump-to-stump line, defended
width outside off, Marsh frees his arms and creams it past the covers. He plays late, cutting it to the right of backward point for four
short on middle, defended to point
short on middle, Warner short-arms it over midwicket with great authority
short and wide outside off, eased to third man
back of a length and outside off, swish and a miss
Marsh camps back and blocks this shortish ball on off
full and outside off, tempts Marsh into a drive. The outside edge is found, it runs away past slip to third man
rising short ball outside off, Warner, however, gets on top of the bounce and pulls to deep midwicket
back of a length and outside off, driven over the covers. Marsh isn't afraid of taking the aerial route
full and bang on middle, pushed back to Boult
full and homing in on the pads, clipped through backward square leg
dug in, Warner leaps off his feet and pulls in the air, behind square
shortish and on off, Marsh gets behind the line in defence
width outside off, flat-bat wallop to mid-off
back of a length and outside off, sliced hit to third man
bouncer, pulled powerfully. Flat towards deep midwicket. Santner makes good ground, slides to his left and keeps it to two
Santner makes a mess of this! Banged in on middle, pulled to the right of Santner. The second bounce is rather awkward and he lets it through to the boundary
short and outside off, Marsh wants for force it away but the ball goes only as far as cover
full and outside off, asking Marsh to drive with two slips in place. Marsh does not hold back, cracks to cover
slides across from round the wicket, slashed to mid-off
pitched up and outside off, hit hard to long-off
drifts in on middle, Marsh bends forward in defence
arm-ball, skids in, blocked
Santner held this back outside off. No problem, says Marsh. He frees his arms and slaps a cut through point. Looped up but the width played against Santner
wicket-to-wicket line, tight stuff. Pushed down the ground
zippy back of a length ball outside off, Marsh does not hold back. He wants to lash another cut. No dice
banged in short on off, rushes onto Marsh. Raps him high on the bat. Miscued over midwicket
Marsh stands tall and punches through cover for one
Warner moves on to 97. Back of a length and on the hips, whipped past midwicket
width outside off, crunched to deep cover
back of a length on off, played up to cover
arm-ball comes in, punched down the ground on the back foot

big appeal for lbw, not given by ump Billy. Did the pitch outside leg? Baz, Ronchi, and Santner have a chat. Santner coaxes his captain to review it. Arrowed in from round the wicket, strikes the back pad. No inside edge involved. Pitched in line, the tracker shows that it would smash the middle of middle stump. No century for Warner. Game-changing incision from Santner?
pushed through quicker, Wade misses the lap sweep. Rapped on the pad
forward and pushed back to the bowler
slides on middle, poked to cover
flighted ball, defended to backward point
short and angled away outside off, punched to backward point
back of a length and outside off, slapped to cover-point, where the fielder fumbles and allows a single
length and outside off, Marsh middles a drive but his placement is't great. He finds cover
full on the stumps, push driven to the left of mid-on
full and outside off, bent-knee drive through covers. It don't look pretty, though
Milne lets rip a bouncer outside off, Wade sways his upper body out of the way
low full toss, drifts in, bunted down to long-on
tucked off the hips to short fine leg

It soars over for a six Milne pulls off a stunning one-handed catch at the edge of the midwicket boundary (allow me to pick up my jaw from the floor). Milne does a Vettori.Wade can't believe this. He drops to his knees. Pushed through short on middle, Wade skips back and nails a pull. It looks destined to go for a six. But Milne takes flight, times his jump to perfection, and comes out with the ball in his left hand. It took some time for the crowd and Milne himself to realise that he had plucked it!
tossed up, Hastings blocks
slides on, driven to mid-on
played back to the bowler
full and outside off, crisp drive to deep cover
short ball, fended to leg
lifter outside off, Hastings drops his hands on it
back of a length on off, dabbed to cover
full on middle, defended back
full on off, clipped to mid-on. A direct hit could have had Hastings
pushed back to the bowler
punchily driven to long-off
pitched up on off, tapped back to the bowler again
a fumble at covers allows Australia some breathing space
flighted and outside off, agricultural slog over midwicket
pushed through outside off, played to cover
short and outside off, he gets on top of the bounce and punches to sweeper cover
shortish, thumped over midwicket
full and on middle, orthodix drive down to long on
dug in short again, might have been a slower ball. Marsh slugs it hard over midwicket, again
width outside off, thrashed square on the off side. Marsh brings up his fifty. He had a great payday the auction as well. Can he finish this match for Australia?
pitched up and outside off, crisp, lovely drive to the left of cover
drifts in on middle, tapped towards long-on
looped up outside off, tempts Hastings into a big shot. Mistimed back to the bowler
chopped square for a quick single, Hastings makes his ground even as his bat gets stuck onto the turf. By the way, brilliant direct-hit. And words can't do justice to NZ's fielding today
slower through the air, defended
whipped towards cow corner
pitched up and outside off, front-foot drive to long-off
full and aimed at off, patted back to the bowler
full and speared at 141ks, chipped over the ducking non-striker. Marsh falls on the floor. He recovers, and hares across for a single
full on off, punchy drive wide of Anderson at mid-off
pitched up on off, strong front-foot drive to long-off
short with plenty of sting and ducks in as Hastings jumps outside leg. He can't ramp it away. Milne appeals for something
banged in at 140ks, just below chest height, dropped defensively to the leg side
full and just a shade outside off, pushed solidly to cover
short of a length and outside off, Marsh takes advantage of the width and crunches off the front foot to the right of backward point, beats the sliding fielder in the deep. Rasping, rasping cut
short again, punched off the hips to long-on
nudged off the pads through backward square leg
short and hurries onto Marsh, chopped to point
back of a length, punched through the cover region
leg-stump ball, picked away through backward square leg for four. A blip in the outfield. Boult slides to his left but fumbles and allows four
Marsh is in the firing line again. Back of a length and outside off, slammed over Marsh. He avoids the blow and falls on the floor. Hastings walks up, gives him a hand, and picks Marsh up
bumper down leg, wild Tait-esque ball. Hastings half-ducks his head out of the way. Wide
very full on off, driven to mid-off
back of a length, Hastings covers up in defence
Milne hits the back of a length again. Hastings calmly defends
pitched up on off, hit to cover. You can't take Baz on
angled in outside off from round the wicket, driven to deep cover
back of a length, smart drop-and-run single to cover. Hastings gets Marsh back on strike with soft hands
full and outside off, Anderson pulls pace off this ball by rolling his fingers over it. Bunted to long-off
back of a length and outside off, late-cut to short third man
shortish and ducks in, punched to mid-on
pitched up on off at 96ks, pushed to long-on
full and attacking the stumps, driven down the ground
shortish and on off, midwicket dives to his left and deflects this punchy stroke towards mid-on
back of a length, he stands tall and punches past short cover
fractionally short and outside off, slashed to short cover
tucked from off stump but short midwicket hunts it down
full and ducks in to ping the pad as Marsh does not connect with a flick
low full toss outside off, Marsh reaches out and squeezes it to mid-off
Boult goes wide of the crease and dupes Marsh with a charming back of the hand slower ball. It just climbs over the middle stump. Marsh slogs and misses
low full toss, hit down the ground
another slower ball outside off, Hastings sits back and forces it over Anderson at mid-off
yorker at the base of off, dug back to Boult
short and wide outside off, Marsh attacks the slower ball, he connects reasonably well. That's enough to force it over mid-off
whipped to square leg now
shortish, punched in front of square on the leg side
shortish, slower ball on the leg stump. The batsman waits for it and pulls it over backward square leg
Hastings steps away outside leg and chops to cover
Henry ends the over with another slower ball, flat-batted to mid-off
short and ducks in with the angle. Hastings sways back and away as he rides it down to third man
low full toss, mis-hit to mid-off, diving stop
slippery bouncer, soars over the batsman to Ronchi. Ump Billy calls it a wide
full and aimed at the base of off, slapped to mid-off, Anderson throws himself to his right and keeps it to a dot
back of a length on off, punched down the ground, but Corey Anderson moves swift to his right at mid-off and cuts it off
full on off, square-driven for one
low full toss, Hastings goes for a leg-side flick and chips it just in front of Baz at short cover. ''He won't give up," says Ian Smith
Hastings backs away outside leg, the bowler errs in length. The low full toss is tonked over midwicket. It exploded from the meat of the bat
bouncer outside off, Hastings throws his hands. Flashes and misses
short on leg, Hastings skips away again, dabbed down to third man
full on the stumps, pushed to mid-on
short, tucks Marsh up for room on the off stump. Back of the hand slower ball, chopped towards cover
full and outside off, another slower one, 120ks, Marsh yanks his bottom hand off the bat and squeezes it to point
Boult nails a yorker on middle and leg, squirted out to mid-off
hint of width outside off, flat-bat belt past mid-off, Hastings sends it thudding to the boundary

Hastings is pumped. Marsh embraces him. Hastings finishes it off with successive fours. Near half-volley length, blugeoned ram-rod straight down the ground. Has Hastings snatched the finishing rights from Faulkner?
